Key Match Events: Wembanyama recorded 29 points, seven rebounds, one assist, three blocks and three turnovers, leading the Spurs to a 109-106 win over the Rockets in a comeback effort by the Rockets.
Post-Match Reflections: Wembanyama kept his cool, dropping 15 points in the first half and 14 in the second half, contributing significantly to the Spurs' dominance in the first half.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Spurs outscored the Rockets 52-42 in the paint and had a 28-21 advantage at the free-throw line.
Wembanyama made good use of his improved size and strength, especially evident in his free-throw attempts.
